flowRoot.flowPara: Here I've created a template for a card. I've grouped it all under a group with id "Card$". This tells DeCCed that this is the object it should copy for each card. Inside that group, I created two text areas called "RankUp$" and "RankDown$". These will be able to have their text replaced with values from a manifest file. I also likewise added to glyphs called "SuitUp$" and "SuitDown$". I added an array of "Pips" I marked as "Pip$1" through "Pip$17". All of these are CLONES of the glyphs to the side. This is important because it creates a link back to the original glyph so any changes to that one affect the pips on the card. These pips I will turn on and off depending on the rank of the card.

Here I've CLONED (i.e. ALT-D) each of the glyphs and placed them on top of each other here. Clone, vs duplicate, simply tells it to reuse the source paths, etc, not to create a copy. This is helpful because I can align them in relation to each other as they will be used on my card as well as I can edit the source glyph above and have the results show up everywhere it's used.
Here I've drawn the suit glyphs I'll use. I've given them id's ending in "Source" so I can easily find them in the XML editor. I've also moved them to the "AssetsLayer".
